You are an AI coding agent working in this repo. Follow these project constraints.

## Tech stack
- Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Vercel AI SDK (`ai`, `@ai-sdk/google`, etc.)
- Notion API (`@notionhq/client`)
- Mermaid.js

## Model usage policy
- Left-side document parsing + Feynman chat: **Gemini 2.5 Flash** (Google provider / SDK).
- Interviewer assessment: **DeepSeek Chat**.
- Prefer robust fallback behavior when Gemini free-tier quota/429 occurs.

## API routing conventions
- All API routes live under `app/api/**/route.ts` using **Route Handlers**.
- Prefer `runtime = "nodejs"` when using Node-only SDKs (Notion, undici agents, etc.).

## Data storage policy
- Persist all user/session/knowledge data via **Notion API**.
- Do **not** introduce any other databases (Postgres/Redis/Supabase/etc.) unless explicitly requested.

## Streaming policy (Vercel limits)
- Vercel Hobby plan serverless timeout is ~10s.
- Any long-running operation must use **streaming**.
- For streaming responses, use Vercel AI SDK `streamText(...)` (and its response helpers) as the standard pattern.

## Learning session writeback policy
- During interview flow, keep intermediate data in **frontend state**.
- At the end, write to Notion **once** (single settlement action), not on every turn.

## Notion rate limit
- Notion API has ~**3 requests/second** rate limit.
- When doing batch writes/updates, implement a request **queue / throttling** mechanism.
- Avoid concurrent bursts of Notion requests from a single route handler.

